<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Verification on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/verification/</link><description>Recent content in Verification on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/verification/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Apple ID Verification Failed Error on Mac</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-apple-id-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-apple-id-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="apple-id-verification-failed-error-on-mac"&gt;Apple ID Verification Failed Error on Mac&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apple ID sign-in fails with &amp;ldquo;Verification failed&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Unable to sign in&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Two-factor authentication failed&amp;rdquo;, or &amp;ldquo;An error occurred during activation&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apple ID verification errors prevent you from signing into iCloud, App Store, or other Apple services. They typically stem from network issues, two-factor authentication problems, or Apple ID account status issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network connectivity issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two-factor authentication code expired or incorrect&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apple ID locked due to security reasons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Date/time settings incorrect&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keychain corruption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apple server outages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-apple-system-status"&gt;Check Apple System Status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Visit &lt;a href="https://www.apple.com/support/systemstatus/"&gt;apple.com/support/systemstatus&lt;/a&gt; to verify Apple services are operational.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Firmware Update Verification Error on Mac</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-firmware-update-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-firmware-update-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="firmware-update-verification-error-on-mac"&gt;Firmware Update Verification Error on Mac&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Firmware update fails with &amp;ldquo;Verification error&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Update failed&amp;rdquo;, or update process hangs during installation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mac firmware updates are applied during macOS installation or system updates. Verification errors occur when the firmware image is corrupted, incompatible with your Mac model, or interrupted during installation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interrupted firmware update&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corrupted firmware download&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mac model incompatibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Power loss during update&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disk errors preventing firmware write&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Security software blocking update&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-firmware-version"&gt;Check Firmware Version&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check current firmware version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;system_profiler SPHardwareDataType | grep &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Model Identifier&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check iBridge version (Apple Silicon)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;system_profiler SPBridgeDataType 2&amp;gt;/dev/null
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check Boot ROM version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ioreg -l -w0 | grep &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;boot-rom-version&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="retry-firmware-update"&gt;Retry Firmware Update&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Ensure stable power connection (desktop: keep plugged in)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Ensure battery &amp;gt; 50% (laptop)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check for updates&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;softwareupdate --list
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Install all updates&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;softwareupdate --install --all
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Restart when prompted&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-power-connection"&gt;Check Power Connection&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Verify power status&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pmset -g batt
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Ensure connected to power&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# For laptops: plug in charger&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# For desktops: verify UPS if applicable&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="reset-smc"&gt;Reset SMC&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Intel Mac with T2:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 1. Shut down Mac&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 2. Hold Ctrl+Option+Shift for 7 seconds&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 3. Also hold power button for 7 more seconds&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 4. Release all keys, wait 5 seconds&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 5. Turn on Mac&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Apple Silicon: NVRAM reset automatic during restart&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-disk-health"&gt;Check Disk Health&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Verify disk is healthy&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;diskutil verifyVolume /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Repair if needed (from Recovery Mode)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;diskutil repairVolume /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="manually-download-update"&gt;Manually Download Update&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Download macOS installer from App Store&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Run installer to reapply firmware&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or download from:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT211683&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="contact-apple-support"&gt;Contact Apple Support&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If firmware update repeatedly fails:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Java VerifyError — Bytecode Verification Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/verifyerror/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/verifyerror/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="verifyerror--bytecode-verification-fix"&gt;VerifyError — Bytecode Verification Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;VerifyError&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when the JVM&amp;rsquo;s bytecode verifier detects that a class file is structurally incorrect or violates the Java Virtual Machine Specification. This is a subclass of &lt;code&gt;LinkageError&lt;/code&gt; and typically indicates that the class file was generated by an incompatible compiler or bytecode manipulation tool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error occurs during the verification phase of class loading. The JVM checks that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bytecode instructions are valid and properly formatted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stack depth is consistent at every instruction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Type usage is consistent (e.g., no mixing of incompatible types).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access control rules are respected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common message variants include:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] macOS Apple ID Sign-In Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-apple-id-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-apple-id-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="macos-apple-id-sign-in-error-fix"&gt;macOS Apple ID Sign-In Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apple ID sign-in errors prevent you from accessing iCloud, App Store, and other Apple services. Messages include &amp;ldquo;Verification Failed,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Apple ID Locked,&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;An error occurred during activation.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apple ID authentication requires a valid session token and network connection to Apple&amp;rsquo;s authentication servers. Failures can be due to incorrect credentials, two-factor authentication issues, or server-side problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect Apple ID password&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two-factor authentication code expired or incorrect&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apple ID locked due to too many failed attempts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Date/time incorrect preventing SSL validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network blocking Apple authentication servers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;macOS keychain corruption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-apple-id-status"&gt;1. Check Apple ID status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Verify Apple ID is not disabled&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Visit https://iforgot.apple.com from another device&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check system date/time&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;date
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo sntp -sS time.apple.com
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-reset-keychain-for-apple-id"&gt;2. Reset keychain for Apple ID&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Open Keychain Access (Applications → Utilities)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Search for &amp;#34;appleid&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Delete all entries related to Apple ID&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Restart the Mac and sign in again&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-sign-in-via-terminal"&gt;3. Sign in via terminal&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check Apple ID account status via System Configuration&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;defaults read /Library/Preferences/SystemConfiguration/com.apple.airport.preferences
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-clear-authentication-cache"&gt;4. Clear authentication cache&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Clear the authentication agent cache&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo defaults delete /Library/Preferences/com.apple.loginwindow RetriesUntilBlank
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;killall AccountsDaemon
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-icloud-error"&gt;iCloud Error&lt;/a&gt; — iCloud sync failures after auth issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="keychain-error"&gt;Keychain Error&lt;/a&gt; — keychain access and unlock errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="nserror-10"&gt;App Store Error&lt;/a&gt; — App Store download failures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] npm Integrity Check Failed</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/npm/npm-integrity-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/npm/npm-integrity-error/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;An npm integrity check failed error occurs when the downloaded package does not match the expected checksum. This indicates potential corruption or tampering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network interruption during download caused corrupted tarball&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;npm registry returned incorrect package content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Local cache contains corrupted package&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Package was modified after publication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mirror registry has stale or incorrect packages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="clear-npm-cache"&gt;Clear npm Cache&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm cache clean --force
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="verify-registry-configuration"&gt;Verify Registry Configuration&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm config get registry
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="reinstall-dependencies"&gt;Reinstall Dependencies&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm install
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-cache-integrity"&gt;Check Cache Integrity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm cache verify
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-official-registry"&gt;Use Official Registry&lt;/h3&gt;
